"{\"abstract\":\"We present a multiscale approach for minimizing the energy associated with Markov Random Fields (MRFs) with energy functions that include arbitrary pairwise potentials. The MRF is represented on a hierarchy of successively coarser scales, where the problem on each scale is itself an MRF with suitably defined potentials. These representations are used to construct an efficient multiscale algorithm that seeks a minimal-energy solution to the original problem. The algorithm is iterative and features a bidirectional crosstalk between fine and coarse representations. We use consistency criteria to guarantee that the energy is nonincreasing throughout the iterative process. The algorithm is evaluated on real-world datasets, achieving competitive performance in relatively short run-times.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3374453\",\"name\":\"Omer Meir\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3374453\"},{\"authorId\":\"2991672\",\"name\":\"M. Galun\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2991672\"},{\"authorId\":\"2072457\",\"name\":\"Stav Yagev\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2072457\"},{\"authorId\":\"1760994\",\"name\":\"R. Basri\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1760994\"},{\"authorId\":\"1699099\",\"name\":\"I. Yavneh\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1699099\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"1612.05441\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"143657159\",\"name\":\"P. Swoboda\"},{\"authorId\":\"16576043\",\"name\":\"B. Andres\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1109/CVPR.2017.530\",\"intent\":[\"methodology\",\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"112f3f1bf15c67b6a627eedef38907562642431b\",\"title\":\"A Message Passing Algorithm for the Minimum Cost Multicut Problem\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/112f3f1bf15c67b6a627eedef38907562642431b\",\"venue\":\"2017 IEEE Conference on Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (CVPR)\",\"year\":2017}